# Claude OS runtime (Cursor)

## Cursor stack (native surfaces)

Use **this rule** (`.cursor/rules/`) together with repo-root **`AGENTS.md`** and the operational tree **`.claude/`** — same runtime as Codex/CLI agents; do not fork a second OS root.

## Single source of truth

All operational state, workflow gates, capability routing, and session scripts live under **`.claude/`**.

- **Capabilities / routing**: read **`.claude/os-capabilities.json`** before suggesting high-risk automation.
- **Session**: **`.claude/session-state.md`**, **`.claude/learning-log.md`**, append-only **`.claude/decision-log.jsonl`** where applicable.
- **Scripts**: prefer **`pwsh .claude/scripts/*.ps1`** (or documented `bash` hooks) already installed by bootstrap.

## What not to do

- Invent a parallel runtime tree (e.g. `.cursor-os/`) — use **`.claude/`** only.
- Broad `git add .` or force-push — follow project **`.agent/operating-contract.md`** and team policy.

## Shared agent contract

**`AGENTS.md`** at the repo root is the cross-tool thin contract; keep Cursor behaviour consistent with it.

**human approval required** for production deploys, auth/billing/PII changes, and schema migrations unless explicitly out of scope.
